Daily Standup
Purpose
Inspects how progress is trending toward completing the work in the Sprint Backlog.
3 Questions
What have you done since the last meeting?
What do you plan to do before the next meeting?
Do you experience any obstacles?
Rules
Adapt the plan for the next 24 hours to ensure that we move
forward toward a successful increment.




Pair Programming

Two member teams, driver and navigator.
Constant reflection, real time review.

Sprint Review Meeting
Purpose
Update what was done during a sprint and any changes during the Product Backlog during the Sprint.  Then evaluate the next things that could be done to optimize value.
Participants
Scrum Master
Scrum Team
External stakeholders, such as technical architects
Timing
4 hours max!!
Location
Same place as sprint meetings
Expected Outcomes
•	The team tells the story of its journey during the Sprint
•	The team delivers the product Increment built during the Sprint to management, customers, users and the Product Owner
•	The team follows the demo meeting with a Sprint Retrospective to learn from their experiences this Sprint
•	PowerPoint presentations are forbidden!


